(1) Notwithstanding section seven, after the commencement of this Act, any person who holds land under customary tenure may convert it into a leasehold tenure not exceeding ninety-nine years on application, in the manner prescribed, by way of— (a) a grant of leasehold by the President; (b) any other title that the President may grant; (c) any other law.
